{
  "id": 5088012836536320,
  "name": " Stop sending Purpose: prefetch header from prefetches and prerenders",
  "summary": "Now that prefetches and prerenders are utilizing the Sec-Purpose header for prefetches and prerenders, we will move to remove the legacy `Purpose: prefetch` header that is still currently passed. This will be behind a feature flag/ kill switch to prevent compatibility issues.\n\nThis will be scoped to speculation rules prefetch, speculation rules prerender, <link rel=prefetch>, and Chromium's non-standard <link rel=prerender>.",
  "markdown_fields": [
    "summary"
  ],
