  "rollout_plan_displayname": "Will ship enabled for all users",
  "motivation": "Each browser uses non-standardized header name that is not aligned with CORS spec (Mozilla's x-moz, chrome's purpose, and Safari doesn't support prefetch yet). As part of standardizing the header names, Sec-Purpose: \"prefetch\" and Sec-Purpose: \"prefetch;prerender\" is used. \n\nThis is to remove current legacy code that still adds the Purpose: prefetch header to maintain the standardized name going into the future.",
